 framework will be evaluated on both simulated environments (using AirSim with perturbed weather, dynamic obstacles, and signal dropouts) and real-world datasets collected under challenging conditions. We expect this approach to reduce navigation drift by at least 40% compared to state-of-the-art VIO and visual-inertial fusion baselines, while increasing mission completion rates in turbulent or visually degraded settings. Potential broader impacts include safer autonomous delivery drones, reliable search-and-rescue UAVs, and foundational advances in trustworthy AI for embodied agents.",
